This memorandum, issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., delegates authority to the Secretary of State regarding certain provisions of the Trafficking Victims Protection Act of 2000. Specifically, the Secretary of State is granted the authority to waive certain prohibitions and issue instructions regarding Afghanistan under section 110(d)(4) of the Act. The Secretary of State must notify the President before exercising this authority. Additionally, the Secretary of State is delegated the authority under section 110(c) of the Act to inform the appropriate congressional committees about such actions and provide justification for them. The memorandum concludes by directing the publication of this document in the Federal Register.